Unionisable Seven Forks hydroelectricity power stations&rsquo; workers evicted their interim officials who had declined to leave for a year. They elected new officials.The workers are under the Mt Kenya East Kenya Electrical Trades and Allied Workers&rsquo; Union branch. They signed petitions demanding that the former officials vacate their posts. They accused them of not calling for polls and clinging to the positions.New chairman Moses Nyambuti and secretary David Nyambuti said the former officials who were expected to organise the elections held their posts illegally. Efforts to hold elections had been futile, they said.The members signed a petitioned presented to the Registrar of Trade Unions, who consented to the elections conducted at the Gitaru hydropower station on Saturday.